      <head>Gottfried Galston</head>

      <div>
        <p>Austrian pianist, piano pupil of Leschetizky in Vienna, also of Jadassohn and Reinecke in
          theory and composition at the Leipzig Conservatory. He taught at the Stern Conservatory,
          Berlin 1903-07; toured widely, eventually settled in St. Louis, USA. His <title level="m"
            >Studienbuch</title> was first published in 1909, 3rd edn Munich, 1920.</p>

        <p>No correspondence between Schenker and Galston is known to survive.</p>
      </div>
